I can't stand this weather... It makes me upset.  Take everyone of the negative emotions from the drop down menu in livejournal, and then you'll know how I feel.  I can't keep the same opinion about one person for more than 5 minutes.  And in the car today I decided I'ld listen to HIM non-stop, further making my situation worse.  I can feel a weight pressuring down on top of me.  My dad really wants me to take everything I do more seriously, but if he knew me like you all do, then he would realize how difficult it is for me to take something serious.  Shit is falling apart.  My great grandma is dieing, I'm scared to get caught under the influence, and finals are coming soon.  

I know I'm just babbling, and I don't expect anyone to say they feel bad for me.  I also don't expect anyone to tell me that it's all gonna be ok, and that I have to get over it.  And frankly, I don't give a fuck about anything any more.  

When will the sun shine and make this feeling go away?

The relationship between friends in a clique is ever changing and so dynamic that one can never predict future feelings towards persons in said clique.  Think about it.  Look at your group of friends and think about how you've felt about each individual in the group.  I doubt it has been the same for more than a year.

Why do we single out a member of a group of friends?  Is it to keep things interesting? Even if you doubt that, and you believe that your friend is being an asshole or doing something stupid, is it possible that maybe you are being the asshole and the one is doing stupid things.  Maybe your friend's not changing into someone worse, maybe you are.

Whoa was I just typing something?

Everyone's getting more mature and having more serious relationships and I'm just not not changing at all...

Maybe it's because im 15

Lately I've been discovering a lot about women.  Over the past week or two, I've realized quite a number of things.

1.  Females will take the "load" off other girls shoulders (when dealing with drama) by over              exagerating the things going on in their life.  They will also say or do anything to make their girlfriends feel better.  This could include hating people, telling lies, or ignoring some people.  This makes the girl having trouble feel like she is justified in her decision to be mad at a certain person.  Whats funny is it all goes away after a week or so.

2. Girls can like any guy and tell all their friends, and the moment one thing goes wrong for her chances, the like for the person is completely erased.

3. Girls have absolutely no sense of humor when it comes to their bodies.  Ask for a picture from a guy when he was his ugliest, and he'll probably give it to you.  Ask the same to a girl, you won't get a thing.  The picture has probably already been burned and buried.

Of course when you all read this (women especially) you're going to say that I'm full of shit and I have absolutely no understanding of women what-so-ever.  Regardless, this text will stay in this journal, even if it makes me look like a total jackass.

      Love,
          JTS
